-- Indian shares fall for third day, hit two-week closing low
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Jun 20, 2014 06:11AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 20 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell for the third straight session on Friday, hitting their lowest close in over two weeks as Mahindra and Mahindra <MAHM.NS> declined on concerns over weak monsoon, while other blue-chips slipped on Iraq violence led risk aversion.

Mahindra and Mahindra provisionally fell 3.1 percent, while ICICI Bank <ICBK.NS> ended 1 percent lower.